{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"serving dish","id":"r150822","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-gES80NbAu60\/XZMwGIhjrQI\/AAAAAAAAaZk\/A2c2_P00OjY6sq0xtshonrsBFu4QfDMhwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_w2LxvQN9LLXtrbQN.png","title":"Sicilian Prawn Salad","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"200 g red onions, sliced thinly (1-2 mm)"},{"content":"30 - 40 g red wine vinegar, to taste"},{"content":"10 g fresh parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"50 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"½ garlic clove              (optional)"},{"content":"40 g freshly squeezed lime juice"},{"content":"½ tsp salt, plus extra to taste"},{"content":"1 pinch ground white pepper"},{"content":"300 g water"},{"content":"500 g large raw prawns, peeled and deveined (approx. 1 kg prawns in their shells)"},{"content":"2 - 4 limes, sliced (2-3 mm)"},{"content":"200 g fennel bulb, sliced thinly (1-2 mm)"},{"content":"400 g cherry tomatoes, halved"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"17 g","fat":"10 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"6 g","calories":"785 kJ \/ 187 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh onions and red wine vinegar into it. Stir to coat and set aside."},{"content":"Place parsley, olive oil, garlic (if using), lime juice, salt and white pepper in mixing bowl and emulsify <b>20 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer dressing to another bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl. Place peeled raw prawns in Varoma dish, sprinkle with 2-3 pinches salt and add 3 slices of lime. Set Varoma in position and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Drain onions through Varoma tray and discard vinegar. Remove Varoma, insert Varoma tray with onions, set Varoma back in position and steam a further <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma."},{"content":"Place onions and fennel on a serving dish, add cherry tomato halves and arrange prawns on top. Drizzle salad with the dressing and garnish with remaining lime slices. Serve at room temperature or chilled."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This bright salad is bursting with fresh Italian flavours. Lightly steamed, the onions become more mellow, and with the tomatoes and fennel they form a delicious backdrop to the juicy prawns.<\/i>","Add toasted pine nuts for extra flavour, as is often done in Sicily.","If using frozen prawns, they should be defrosted before starting the recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","40m","6 portions"]}